					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4073241#post-3621018</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4073241/scp-3780#post-3621018</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 27 Oct 2017 17:04:38 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Jacob Conwell</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1372582</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Holy hell, this got a good laugh from me. The anomaly itself is simple, but seeing how various players in the SCPverse use their tools to attempt to stop JFK's death is incredibly entertaining.</p> <p>You definitely made the right call in shifting the focus away from the &quot;What if JFK lives&quot; question, and the fact that him surviving does little to change the base timeline gives the struggle of those attempting to stop the assassination an enjoyable futility.</p> <p>I'd argue that you could probably get a solid collab log out of expanding the assassination attempts portion, however, as is this is a fun, short skip that I must upvote.</p> <p>+1 ARD</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
